ry application at `(head_dim,pair_index,position)` (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-137 Implement HolyC `RoPEQ16RotateHeadByPositionChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to apply checked rotary updates across all `(x,y)` pairs in one head slice with stride/capacity guards for WS5 attention kernels (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-138 Implement HolyC `RoPEQ16RotateHeadRangeByPositionChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to apply checked rotary updates across contiguous head slices (`head_count`, `head_stride_cells`) with per-head base overflow/capacity guards for WS5 attention kernels (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-139 Add host-side parity harness `tests/test_rope_q16_rotate_head_range_position.py` to validate range-wise head rotation contracts (base/stride/capacity/overflow) against per-head composition references (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-140 Implement HolyC helper `RoPEQ16ComputeHeadBaseIndexChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` for checked `head_base + head_index*head_stride_cells` derivation reused by range rotation kernels (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-141 Implement HolyC helper `RoPEQ16ValidateHeadRangeCapacityChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to centralize head-range bounds/overflow checks before multi-head in-place rotation (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-142 Implement HolyC helper `RoPEQ16ValidateHeadSpanForDimChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to centralize checked `{head_base + ((head_dim/2)-1)*pair_stride + 1 < head_cell_capacity}` bounds validation for per-head rotate kernels before pair iteration (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-143 Implement HolyC helper `RoPEQ16ValidateHeadRangeSpanForDimChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to preflight per-head last-pair span bounds (`head_base + ((head_dim/2)-1)*pair_stride + 1`) across `head_count` before multi-head rotation loops (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-144 Add host-side parity harness `tests/test_rope_q16_validate_head_range_span_for_dim.py` for range-span preflight helper with overflow and capacity adversarial cases (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-145 Implement HolyC helper `RoPEQ16RotateHeadRangeByPositionPreflightedChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` that composes range-capacity + range-span preflight helpers then applies per-head rotation for one position (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-146 Implement HolyC helper `RoPEQ16RotateHeadRangeByTokenWindowChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to apply checked head-range rotation across `token_count` positions with checked `position_start + token_index*position_step` math and fail-fast preflight reuse (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-147 Add host-side parity harness `tests/test_rope_q16_rotate_head_range_token_window.py` for token-window range rotation contract and overflow/capacity adversarial cases against per-position composition references (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-148 Implement HolyC `RoPEQ16RotateHeadRangeByTokenWindowPreflightedChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to run range-capacity + range-span preflight once, then apply checked per-token window rotation without partial writes on span faults (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-149 Implement HolyC `RoPEQ16RotateHeadRangeByTokenWindowPreflightedHeadBasesChecked` in `src/model/rope.HC` to precompute and validate per-head base indices once, then reuse them across token-window loops with overflow-safe checked position stepping (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-150 Implement HolyC `RoPEQ16RotateHeadRangeByTokenWindowPreflightedHeadBasesChecked` execution path in `src/model/rope.HC` with a precomputed head-base index buffer reused across all token iterations and strict checked capacity/overflow contracts (WS5-01)\n- [x] IQ-151 Implement HolyC `FPQ16MulDivRoundedChecked` in `src/math/fixedpoint.HC` for checked `(a*b)/d` with one rounding step (overflow/domain-safe) to support RMSNorm and softmax scaling paths (WS1-01)\n- [x] IQ-152 Implement HolyC `FPQ16MulDivRoundedByPositiveIntChecked` in `src/math/fixedpoint.HC` for checked `(a*b)/d_int` fast path (`d_int>0`) with half-up rounding and overflow contracts for RMSNorm denominator specialization (WS1-01)\n- [x] IQ-153 Implement HolyC `FPQ16MulDivRoundedByPositiveIntFromQ16DenChecked` in `src/math/fixedpoint.HC` to accept positive integer denominators encoded as Q16 whole numbers (`den_q16 = n<<16`) and route through the positive-int fast path with strict divisibility/domain contracts for RMSNorm call sites (WS1-01)\n- [x] IQ-154 Implement HolyC `FPQ16RMSNormApplyInvDenomChecked` in `src/math/rmsnorm.HC` to apply precomputed inverse denominator scaling via checked one-rounding mul/div helpers (Q16 denominator contract) and return explicit error codes for WS5 norm call chains (WS1-04)\n- [x] IQ-155 Implement HolyC `FPQ16RMSNormApplyInvDenomWeightedChecked` in `src/math/rmsnorm.HC` to compose checked inverse-denominator scaling with per-channel gamma multiply and explicit BAD_PARAM/OVERFLOW surfaces for WS5 transformer norm paths (WS1-04)\n- [x] IQ-156 Implement HolyC `FPQ16RMSNormApplyInvDenomWeightedInPlaceChecked` in `src/math/rmsnorm.HC` to support alias-safe in-place weighted norm writes (`input_q16 == output_q16`) with the same checked denominator and overflow contracts (WS1-04)\n- [x] IQ-157 Implement HolyC `FPQ16RMSNormApplyInvDenomWeightedAutoChecked` in `src/math/rmsnorm.HC` to dispatch between in-place and out-of-place weighted inverse-denominator paths based on pointer aliasing while preserving identical checked error surfaces (WS1-04)\n- [x] IQ-158 Implement HolyC helper `FPQ16RMSNormApplyInvDenomWeightedAutoValidateChecked` in `src/math/rmsnorm.HC` to centralize null/len/denominator/gamma capacity checks shared by auto-dispatch RMSNorm entrypoints (WS1-04)\n- [x] IQ-159 Implement HolyC helper `FPQ16RMSNormApplyInvDenomWeightedAutoSelectPathChecked` in `src/math/rmsnorm.HC` to derive deterministic in-place vs out-of-place dispatch from pointer aliasing and preserve shared error surfaces (WS1-04)\n- [x] IQ-160 Add host-side parity harness `tests/test_rmsnorm_apply_inv_denom_weighted_auto_checked.py` covering alias/non-alias dispatch equivalence and BAD_PARAM/OVERFLOW parity against explicit in-place/out-of-place references (WS1-04)\n- [x] IQ-161 Implement HolyC helper `FPQ16ExpClampTo